.TH "platform_device_alloc" 9 "platform_device_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
platform_device_alloc \- create a platform device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct platform_device *" platform_device_alloc
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "int id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
base name of the device we're adding
.IP "id" 12
instance id
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a platform device object which can have other objects attached
to it, and which will have attached objects freed when it is released.
